#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:4
msgid "Moving a website to another server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:6
msgid "Before moving your website, make sure you have backed up your data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:8
msgid ""
"Dump your database, using classic ``mysqldump`` or ``pg_dump`` tools. If "
"you’re using *MySQL* ``bin/roadiz database:dump -c`` command can speed-up"
" the process by naming automatically your file against your *app-"
"namespace*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:9
msgid ""
"Archive your files using ``bin/roadiz files:export``, Roadiz will create "
"a ZIP file with your public/private documents and fonts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:12
msgid "Moving to a SSH+Git hosting plan or an other development machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:14
msgid ""
"From this point you can install your new web-server, as described in "
":ref:`Install section <installation>`. Pay attention that if your theme "
"needs some additional *composer* dependencies you should *clone/copy* it "
"into your *themes/* folder **before** running ``composer install --no-"
"dev``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:18
msgid "Then import your dump and files into your new server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:20
msgid ""
"Once you’ve imported your database, you must edit manually your "
"`conf/config.yml`, you can reuse the former server’s one and adapt its "
"database credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:24
msgid ""
"**Do not perform any schema update if no app/gen-src/GeneratedNodeSources"
" classes is available**, it will erase your NodesSources data as their "
"entities files haven’t been generated yet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:27
msgid ""
"When you have edited your ``app/conf/config.yml`` file, regenerate your "
"*Doctrine* entities class files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:33
msgid "Now you can perform a schema update without losing your nodes data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:45
msgid ""
"If you are using an OPcode cache like XCache or APC, you’ll need to purge"
" cache manually because it can't be done from a CLI interface as they are"
" shared cache engines. The most effective way is to restart your *PHP-"
"FPM* service or *Apache* if your are using *mod_php*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:50
msgid "Install assets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:52
msgid ""
"By default, web theme assets are not tracked by *Git*. Make sure that you"
" installed every theme assets using ``bin/roadiz themes:assets:install`` "
"command. You should use ``--symlink --relative`` options when possible to"
" prevent updating assets manually. For Windows users, remove "
"``--relative`` option to create *absolute* symlinks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:65
msgid ""
"*composer.json* file should execute Roadiz default themes asset install "
"automatically after each update or install."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:69
msgid "Synchronize documents and fonts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:71
msgid ""
"You can move your ``files/`` folder using SFTP but the best way is to use"
" ``rsync`` command as it will upload only newer files and it is much "
"faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:81
msgid ""
"It works in the other way too. If you want to work on your local copy "
"with up to date files and fonts, you can download actual files from the "
"production website:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:93
msgid "Moving to a non-SSH hosting plan"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:95
msgid ""
"You have nearly finished your brand new website using Roadiz. You have "
"been working on your own server using Git and Composer, up to this point "
"everything went well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:98
msgid ""
"Now you have to push to production, but your prod-server has no SSH "
"connection. You are stuck with an SFTP connection or worst, an old FTP "
"one. Don’t panic, it will take a little more time but it is still "
"possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:102
msgid ""
"Many shared-plan hosting companies offer you only one or two databases. "
"When moving a Roadiz website, make sure that your database is empty and "
"do not contain orphan tables, you must respect the rule “One app = One "
"database”."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:106
msgid ""
"If you can ZIP on your production server or if you are going to push your"
" files via FTP, do not forget to exclude ``.git`` and ``node_modules`` "
"folders! These folders have **lots** of useless files for a production "
"SSH-less environment. Here is a sample ZIP command to exclude them: ``zip"
" -r mywebsite.zip mywebsite/ -x \"mywebsite/.git/*\" "
"\"mywebsite/themes/**/static/node_modules/*\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:112
msgid ""
"Before transferring your website, make sure you have ``.htaccess`` file "
"in every sensitive folders. You can use the ``bin/roadiz "
"generate:htaccess`` on your computer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:113
msgid ""
"If you have at least SFTP, you should have to rights to zip/unzip on your"
" distant server. So zip the whole Roadiz folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:114
msgid ""
"If you only have FTP, you must be prepared to transfer your Roadiz "
"folder, file-by-file. Just get yourself a nice cup of coffee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:115
msgid ""
"Once everything is copied on your production server, verify than you have"
" the same files as on your dev-server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:116
msgid "Import your database dump with phpmyadmin or pgmyadmin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:117
msgid "Edit your ``conf/config.yml`` to match your new database credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:118
msgid ""
"Verify that root ``.htaccess`` file contains every information to enable "
"Apache url-rewriting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:119
msgid "Try to connect to your website"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/developer/first-steps/moving.rst:120
msgid ""
"If it doesn’t work or display anything, read your PHP log file to "
"understand where the problem comes from. It might be your database "
"credentials or an outdated PHP version. Check that your hosting manager "
"has installed every needed PHP extensions, see :ref:`getting-started`."
msgstr ""

